The paper discusses the use of blockchain technology in various applications such as cryptocurrencies, self-sovereign identities, and transparent voting systems, which are all related to computer security (cs.CR) and cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also talks about decentralization, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper raises questions about the social implications of using decentralized technology, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
